cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and common sense reasoning. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves developing an automatic system that uses machine learning techniques to improve performance on the Winograd Schema Challenge. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves querying a search engine to gather relevant information, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the societal implications of developing systems that can reason and make decisions based on common sense knowledge.
